# Fix: Empty assistant bubble when switching conversations mid-stream

## Context

When the user sends a message and switches to another conversation before any text tokens arrive from the SSE stream (e.g., during the model's initial thinking delay), then switches back, the original conversation shows an empty assistant bubble (just the "ASSISTANT" header with no content).

**Root cause**: Two issues in `AgentContext.tsx`:
1. The message cache saves empty assistant messages (created with `content: ''` at stream start, no text received yet)
2. The cache is always preferred over backend data, even when the backend has a more complete response (the `finally` block in `agent.py` persists whatever text was generated before disconnect)

## Fix (2 changes in `AgentContext.tsx`)

### Change 1: Filter empty assistant messages from cache

In both `loadMessages` (line ~660-672) and `clearMessages` (line ~708-720), after building the `cleaned` array, filter out assistant messages that have no content AND no meaningful segments before caching.

```typescript
// After: const cleaned = prev.map(m => { ... });
// Add filter to remove empty assistant messages
const toCache = cleaned.filter(m => {
  if (m.role === 'assistant' && !m.content?.trim() && (!m.segments || m.segments.length === 0)) {
    return false;
  }
  return true;
});
messagesCacheRef.current.set(outgoingConversationId, toCache);
```

### Change 2: Prefer backend when cache has fewer messages

Change the cache comparison logic (line ~634-641) to only prefer cache when it has at least as many messages as the backend response.

```typescript
// Before:
if (cached && cached.length > 0) {
  finalMsgs = cached;
}

// After:
if (cached && cached.length > 0 && cached.length >= msgs.length) {
  finalMsgs = cached;
}
```

